Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Halve, seed, and remove the white ribs from the @green bell pepper{1}, then cut into 1-inch cubes. Zest and juice the @orange{1}. Quarter the @zucchini{1} lengthwise, then cut into 2-inch sticks. Trim and discard the bottom inch of the @asparagus{1%bunch}. Cut the @Yukon gold potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch cubes. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}.

Toss the zucchini, bell pepper, asparagus, and potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Place in the oven to roast for ~{20-25%minutes}, until lightly caramelized.

Meanwhile, make the marinade: strip @rosemary{1%sprig} leaves off the sprig and finely chop. In a #shallow dish{}, combine the @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoon}, garlic, orange zest, orange juice, rosemary, @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, and a large pinch of salt and pepper. Reserve half this marinade, then add the @steak{12%ounce} to the dish and flip to coat in the marinade. Set aside for ~{5%minutes}.

> This is a great time to get a jump-start on your cleanup!

Heat @oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season steak with salt and pepper on both sides. Add the steak to the pan and cook ~{3-5%minutes} per side, until cooked to desired doneness. Set the steak aside to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

While the steak rests, remove the #baking sheet{} from the oven and heat broiler to high or the oven to 500 degrees. Toss the vegetables with the reserved marinade, return to the oven to broil for ~{2-3%minutes}, until vegetables are glazed.

> Watch carefully, some broilers can get hotter than others!

Thinly slice the steak against the grain and serve with the glazed vegetables to the side. Enjoy!